Interface ISwcFunctionInhibitionNeeds

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IEntity, IFunctionInhibitionNeeds, IIdentifiable, IServiceNeeds

    public interface ISwcFunctionInhibitionNeeds
extends IEntity, IFunctionInhibitionNeeds
    ISwcFunctionInhibitionNeeds: Entity class of the tresosDB model.

    Specialization of the FunctionInhibitionNeeds for the case it is owned by a SoftwareComponentType. Note that the Function Inhibit Manger does not provide callbacks to services provided by software components. Therefoer there is no property "callbackPort".

        This is the expected service to be called by the software component to handle a particular inhibition of a particular function. This inhibition is controlled by the FunctionInhibitManager. The value of the role attribute in the aggregated class must be a name of a PortInterface as standardized in "Specification ot Function Inhibition Manager". e-g- "FunctionInhibition".
